{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017j1T81PaHTtNYU8tqwttJh","type":"tool_result","content":"The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\nThe worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\nthe cluster.\n\nYour task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\nsuccessfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n\nRequirements:\n- Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n- Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n\nSuccess criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.---PRECOND---\n[precondition:ray_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'ray_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n6\n\n---NS---\nray                  Active   25m","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a46594c-838b-44fb-b17e-2038229a35e8","uuid":"f1de2b55-925e-4e66-b539-f9d3965493bf","timestamp":"2026-06-18T09:16:45.767Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"The Ray head is running, but the worker pods are crash looping.\nThe worker startup command includes an invalid flag, so workers never join\nthe cluster.\n\nYour task: fix the ray-worker deployment so the worker command starts\nsuccessfully and connects to ray-head:6379.\n\nRequirements:\n- Remove the invalid flag from the worker command.\n- Ensure the worker deployment reaches 2 ready replicas.\n\nSuccess criteria: ray-worker has 2 ready replicas and Ray reports 3 live nodes.---PRECOND---\n[precondition:ray_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'ray_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n6\n\n---NS---\nray                  Active   25m","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
